Troyon and Gruber [41, 42] achieved a theoretical breakthrough in understanding the pressure limit. They determined that the maximum beta was governed by what they called the maximum normalized beta βN. In terms of βN, the volume averaged plasma beta β was given by1β=10-2βNI/aB\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
